x4freetext: Details of the photon tagging system.
The tagged photons were used as a  source
of the incident-projectile beam.
For the determination of gamma-quantum energy
in  the  tagged  photon method and for the timing of
neutron time-of-flight  measurement  in  (gamma,p+n)
experiment.
For determination of neutron energy.
The  NE213 liquid scintillator cells were used
for registration of neutrons.
A natural  graphite  block of 37 g/cm2 thick was used
in (gamma,n) and (gamma,n+p) experiments.
Correction for the neutron detector efficiency.

x4freetext: No    information    about    source    of
uncertainties.
The photoneutron and  the  photoproton  spectra  from
C-12  were  measured in the excitation energy region
20-100 MeV.  The  differential  cross  sections  for
C-12(gamma,n)   and   C-12(gamma,p)  reactions  were
deduced from the spectra.  In the excitation  energy
region above the giant resonances and below the pion
threshold the importance of one nucleon  process  in
the  photon  absorption  mechanisms  of  nuclei  was
proposed.
Compiled   in   SCJAD  of  Saratov  State
University.
BIB correction.

x4freetext: The high limit of the excitation energy after neutron
emission.
The differential   cross  section  for  C-12(gamma,n)
reaction  leaving  residual  nuclei  around   ground
states was deduced from  the spectra.  Summation  of
the spectra  over all photon energies  was performed
from  the ground  state  to about  5 MeV  excitation
energy.
Data from Fig. 3 of 84OSAKA,,525,1984.
